{"componentChunkName":"component---src-templates-post-js","path":"/posts/2019-12-20-custom-fonts-in-react-native/","result":{"data":{"markdownRemark":{"html":"<h3>Version of react-native > 0.60</h3>\n<p>Firstly download your fonts from <strong><a href=\"https://fonts.google.com/\">Google Fonts</a></strong>. Suppose you have downloaded <code class=\"language-text\">Lato</code> font. Then create an <code class=\"language-text\">assets</code> folder, <code class=\"language-text\">react-native.config.js</code> file into your react-native's root directory and copy all the <code class=\"language-text\">.ttf</code> files extracted from  downloaded <code class=\"language-text\">zip</code> file. Add following codes into <code class=\"language-text\">react-native.config.js</code> file.</p>\n<div class=fakeMenu>\n</div>\n<div class=\"gatsby-highlight\" data-language=\"javascript\"><pre class=\"language-javascript\"><code class=\"language-javascript\">module<span class=\"token punctuation\">.</span>exports <span class=\"token operator\">=</span> <span class=\"token punctuation\">{</span>\n  project<span class=\"token operator\">:</span> <span class=\"token punctuation\">{</span>\n    ios<span class=\"token operator\">:</span> <span class=\"token punctuation\">{</span><span class=\"token punctuation\">}</span><span class=\"token punctuation\">,</span>\n    android<span class=\"token operator\">:</span> <span class=\"token punctuation\">{</span><span class=\"token punctuation\">}</span>\n  <span class=\"token punctuation\">}</span><span class=\"token punctuation\">,</span>\n  assets<span class=\"token operator\">:</span> <span class=\"token punctuation\">[</span><span class=\"token string\">'./assets/fonts/'</span><span class=\"token punctuation\">]</span>\n<span class=\"token punctuation\">}</span></code></pre></div>\n<p>Then run this command in your project's directory.</p>\n<div class=fakeMenu>\n  <div class=\"fakeButtons fakeClose\"></div>\n  <div class=\"fakeButtons fakeMinimize\"></div>\n  <div class=\"fakeButtons fakeZoom\"></div>\n</div>\n<div class=\"gatsby-highlight\" data-language=\"bash\"><pre class=\"language-bash\"><code class=\"language-bash\">$ react-native <span class=\"token function\">link</span></code></pre></div>\n<p>Add <strong><code class=\"language-text\">fontFamily: &#39;Lato-Bold&#39;</code></strong> in your <code class=\"language-text\">StyleSheet</code> and run</p>\n<div class=fakeMenu>\n  <div class=\"fakeButtons fakeClose\"></div>\n  <div class=\"fakeButtons fakeMinimize\"></div>\n  <div class=\"fakeButtons fakeZoom\"></div>\n</div>\n<div class=\"gatsby-highlight\" data-language=\"bash\"><pre class=\"language-bash\"><code class=\"language-bash\">$ react-native run-android</code></pre></div>\n<p>Hopefully you can see your added font.</p>","timeToRead":1,"frontmatter":{"template":"post","title":"Add Custom Fonts in React Native Android","featuredImage":{"childImageSharp":{"fixed":{"base64":"data:image/png;base64,","width":100,"height":100,"src":"/static/83be406408af0c056f27c89be17da6ed/71eb7/react-native.png","srcSet":"/static/83be406408af0c056f27c89be17da6ed/71eb7/react-native.png 1x,\n/static/83be406408af0c056f27c89be17da6ed/92ab1/react-native.png 1.5x"}}},"date":"20 December, 2019","category":["React-Native"],"tags":["react-native"]},"excerpt":"Version of react-native > 0.60 Firstly download your fonts from Google Fonts. Suppose you have downloaded  font. Then create an  folderâ€¦","fields":{"slug":"/posts/2019-12-20-custom-fonts-in-react-native/"}}},"pageContext":{"slug":"/posts/2019-12-20-custom-fonts-in-react-native/"}}}